06/05/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Croatian President Stipe Mesic told reporters Monday (5 May) that countries in the region should introduce EU standards and liberalise travel regimes. 
He also proposed a bilateral agreement regulating a visa-free regime between Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro, and reiterated his country's commitment to cross-border co-operation in crime fighting. 
(Danas, HINA - 05/05/03)
